      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's completely understandable that those platitudes feel empty when you're feeling this deeply disconnected. The idea of fading away sounds peaceful because the weight of constantly trying to be *seen* is exhausting. If the world feels like it would keep moving without you, that feeling of relief is a very real signal that you are in deep pain. Please consider letting someone know how much this emptiness is hurting you right now; there are people who want to listen without judgment.",
      "source": "target",
